# Platform quirks (Windows / this project)

## Shell & heredoc
- This machine runs **PowerShell on Windows**. Bash heredocs (`<<'EOF'`) do NOT work natively.
- When writing files in Vercel Sandbox or similar remote environments, always prefer SDK methods (`sandbox.writeFiles()`) over `bash -c cat <<EOF` to avoid both heredoc incompatibility and OS argument-length limits (`argument list too long`).

## Vercel Sandbox file writes
- Use `sandbox.writeFiles([{ path, content: Buffer.from(str, "utf-8") }])` instead of shell heredocs.
- The OS `exec` arg limit (~2 MB) is easily hit with large generated codebases (20+ files).

## Playwright / Inspector
- `INSPECTOR_CAPTURE_WORKER_URL` is often unset locally. Inspector endpoints (`element-map`, `capture`) have local Playwright fallbacks via `chromium.launch()`.
- Ensure Playwright browsers are installed: `npx playwright install chromium`.

## Stream proxy (long v0 generations)
- Never call `reader.releaseLock()` while a `reader.read()` is pending — use `reader.cancel()` in `ReadableStream.cancel()` callbacks instead, to avoid `ERR_INVALID_STATE`.
